3. Space DMV v1.0 Spec Document (high-level)

You can treat this as a starting spec for internal docs or a GitHub README.

---

3.1 Overview

Name: Space DMV Core Platform (SDCP‑1.0)
Version: 1.0 (Prototype)
Role: Civilian coordination and training platform for hybrid and space mobility.
Scope: Identity orchestration, DVV registry, safety protocols, and operator UX.

---

3.2 Components

3.2.1 Unified Login Portal (ULP‑1.0)

Responsibilities:

• Present login options: DMV‑O, FAAO, Space‑O.
• Handle OAuth/OIDC flows.
• Assemble Identity Envelope (IE‑1.0).


Non-responsibilities:

• Storing identity data.
• Acting as an identity provider.


---

3.2.2 Identity Envelope (IE‑1.0)

Fields (conceptual):

• operator_id (internal, non-legal)
• legal_name
• dmv_token (optional)
• faa_token (optional)
• space_token (optional)
• safety_profile• gravity_range
• access_needs
• non_violent_pledge (boolean)

• mission_context


Usage:

• Access control
• Safety protocol selection
• Training flow personalization


---

3.2.3 DVV Registry

Entity: DVV

• dvv_id (unique)
• vessel_name
• vessel_class (e.g., ground-air-space-hybrid, orbital-shuttle, sim-only)
• owner_operator_id (link to operator)
• capabilities (domains, ranges, limits)
• safety_rating
• maintenance_log (summary, not raw data)
• emergency_profile


APIs (conceptual):

• GET /dvv/{dvv_id} — read-only lookup
• POST /dvv — create (Space DMV only)
• PATCH /dvv/{dvv_id} — update (Space DMV only)


External access:

• DMV/FAA can call GET /dvv/{dvv_id} with proper auth.


---

3.2.4 Safety Protocol Engine (SPC‑1.0)

Inputs:

• Identity Envelope
• DVV record
• Mission context


Outputs:

• Required safety steps
• Training recommendations
• Warnings / constraints (e.g., “not approved for high-G maneuvers”)


Example rules:

• If gravity_range = "low" → avoid high-G training scenarios.
• If mission_type = "family_shuttle" → enable kid-safe briefing mode.
• If vessel_class = "hybrid" → require hybrid transition training.


---

3.2.5 Operator Console

Features (v1.0):

• View/edit safety profile (gravity, access needs, pledge).
• View linked DVVs.
• Start a mission (select vessel + mission type).
• Launch training modules.
• View ceremonial “license journey” progress.


---

3.3 Non-Goals (v1.0)

• No issuance of legal licenses or certifications.
• No direct modification of DMV or FAA records.
• No mandatory participation for any state or operator.
• No surveillance or behavioral scoring.


---

3.4 Implementation Notes (Prototype Level)

• Front-end can be static HTML/JS (like your current Space DMV demo).
• Identity and DVV can be mocked locally for now.
• Safety Protocol Engine can start as a simple rules engine in JavaScript.
• All “real” integrations (DMV/FAA) can be simulated with stub APIs until there’s a real partner.


